# Code owners for the Terrain repository.
#
# GitHub uses this file to auto-request reviews on pull requests touching
# matching paths. Branch-protection rules can be configured to require
# owner approval before merging — that gating is set in the GitHub UI,
# not here.
#
# Wildcards work like .gitignore. The last matching pattern wins, so
# more-specific overrides go below the catch-all.
#
# Today the repo has a single primary maintainer; this file documents
# that explicitly so external contributors know who reviews their work
# and so future co-maintainers can be added by simply listing them.

* @PMCLSF

# Release-engineering surfaces deserve extra eyes when present:
# anything that touches signing, distribution, or reproducibility should
# be reviewed by whoever currently owns release pipeline work.
/.github/workflows/release.yml @PMCLSF
/.goreleaser.yaml @PMCLSF
/bin/terrain-installer.js @PMCLSF
/bin/postinstall.js @PMCLSF

